The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Oct. 18: The government has formed a committee with representations from Sebi, the CBI and the Enforcement Directorate to expedite investigation in the Satyam Computer accounting scam. The coordination committee will be headed by additional secretary to the ministry of corporate affairs, official sources said. We want to finish the investigation by the end of this year, an official said.                            
	 New Delhi, Oct. 18: The cabinet committee on economic affairs is expected to take up tomorrow the commerce ministrys proposal to release inflation data on a monthly basis and not every week for the bulk of the items tracked by the wholesale price index.                            
	 New Delhi, Oct. 18: The New Pension Scheme has drawn Rs 3.5 crore from over 2,000 accounts within more than five months of its introduction. According to PFRDA data, 2,183 accounts have been opened by the collection and distribution centres, known as points of presence.                            
	 New Delhi, Oct. 18: Indian firms engaged in man-made fibre business are drawing up expansion plans to ramp up capacities. According to a CMIE study, nine projects were announced in the second quarter ended September.                             
	 New Delhi, Oct. 18: Market regulator Sebi will come up with guidelines for setting up stock exchanges exclusively for small and medium firms soon. Sebi is working on it. The norms are being finalised and will be released soon, finance ministry sources said.                                                                                                                           
